 290:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * in the intialization structure. If the oversampling value is set to 0 in the structure, the defa
 291:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * is considered. Sampling point for each symbol is configured at the half of sampling period. Symb
 292:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * majority decision among 3 samples.
 293:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Word length is configured with the number of data bits. If the value of \a frame_length is 0, th
 294:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * is set to the same value as word length. If \a frame_length is greater than 0, it is set as the 
 295:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Parity mode is set to the value configured for \a parity_mode.
 296:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * The USIC channel should be set to UART mode by calling the XMC_UART_CH_Start() API after the ini
 297:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  *
